<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="deaf-adj">deaf <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /def/    美 /def/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>聋的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>become / go deaf</strong>
变聋</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>be deaf in one ear 
一只耳朵聋了</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Deaf people are very attentive in almost every aspect of life. 
失聪的人对生活几乎每个方面都很专注。</p><footer>2011 安徽</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>不愿听：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>be <strong>deaf to</strong> all advice / requests
对一切劝告/要求充耳不闻</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="turn-a-deaf-ear-to">turn a deaf ear (to)</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(对…) 置之不理：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Many of them turned a deaf ear to his advice, even though they knew it to be valuable. 
他们中的许多人对他的建议置之不理，即使他们知道他的建议是有益的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">派生词汇</h2>
<p>deafen /'defn/ vt [常用于被动语态]   </p></div>